The Federal Government today celebrated the nationâ€™s 59th independence anniversary at the Presidential Villa, Abuja with a vibrant display by the Presidential change of guard from 177 guard battalion to 7th battalion of the guards brigade.  It was the highpoint of the week-long activities marking the anniversary as President Buhari inspected the quarter guards, and then walked to the Villa forecourt to receive national salute which was followed by rendition of the National Anthem.  In attendance at the ceremony were the Vice President; Prof. Yemi Osinbanjo, Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, and the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, the Chief Justice of Nigeria, Ibrahim Tanko Mohammad, the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), Boss Mustapha, Service chiefs and other top government functionaries and members of the diplomatic corps.  Our State House Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that there was also 21 gun salute in honour of President Buhari, signing of the anniversary register, cutting of the anniversary cake amongst others.  Speaking with State House Correspondents after the ceremony at the Presidential Villa, the Senate President, Ahmed Lawan and the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila urged Nigerians to remain united saying Nigeria has come a long way as one indivisible entity, which every citizen must work to protect.  The Secretary General of the Federation, Mr Boss Mustapha and Minister Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed in separate interviews called for positive attitudinal change as Nigeria faces numerous challenges which they say is surmountable. 